1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,600
<i>According to what
we've gathered,</i>

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:12,833
<i>one of the guys who beat you up</i>

3
00:00:12,967 --> 00:00:14,867
<i>lives in the place
we're heading to.</i>

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,167
<i>I think I recognize
the other one.</i>

5
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:17,367
<i> So what do we do now?</i>

6
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,833
<i>Looks like you guys need
to warm up.</i>

7
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:21,533
<i>So, it was the sniper who cut
these cables too?</i>

8
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:23,733
<i>The one who killed Lieutenant
Robles must be a professional.</i>

9
00:00:23,867 --> 00:00:25,833
<i>Works efficiently
and is also smart.</i>

10
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:28,567
<i>I understand you're worried
because she's your sister,</i>

11
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:30,367
<i> but you also know our clients.</i>

12
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:31,833
<i> I'll take care of them.</i>

13
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:35,233
<i>The important thing is, no one
will know about our operation.</i>

14
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,233
<i> Hands up!</i>

15
00:00:36,367 --> 00:00:37,333
<i> What's going on here?</i>

16
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:38,367
<i> I knew it!</i>

17
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,867
<i>My suspicion about this guy
was right.</i>

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,000
<i> We're all in the same boat.</i>

19
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:43,100
<i>I'm also investigating
a murder case here.</i>

20
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:44,467
<i>Is this the one
who killed Regan?</i>

21
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,733
<i> Yes, Sir.</i>

22
00:00:45,867 --> 00:00:48,700
<i>A garbage collector saw him
cutting the CCTV cables.</i>

23
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:50,400
<i>Everything that's happening
is connected.</i>

24
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:51,367
<i>Where are Conde and the others?</i>

25
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,600
<i> I'm a private investigator.</i>

26
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:54,433
<i>Miss Addison
of Add2Cart hired me</i>

27
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:56,367
<i>to investigate the death
of their daughter.</i>

28
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:57,933
<i> That's why her mother suspects</i>

29
00:00:58,067 --> 00:00:59,567
<i>that a foul play
really happened.</i>

30
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,667
<i>Why didn't she ask
the police for help?</i>

31
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:02,833
<i> She brought it to you.</i>

32
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:04,433
<i> To Station 12 itself.</i>

33
00:01:04,567 --> 00:01:07,533
<i>But she felt the cop
handling the case buried it</i>

34
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:08,500
<i> so it wouldn't be solved.</i>

35
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:09,900
<i> Do you know who that cop is?</i>

36
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:12,733
<i> Lieutenant Regan Robles.</i>

37
00:01:15,667 --> 00:01:17,600
They killed Regan Robles

38
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:21,900
when we found out he was
a member of a syndicate.

39
00:01:22,033 --> 00:01:23,667
Lieutenant Conde...

40
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,900
if Regan handled the case,

41
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:30,200
that means the syndicate
is involved in Miss Calabri.

42
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:32,267
That's my suspicion here.

43
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,600
There's prostitution going on.

44
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:38,500
The contestants who don't agree
are the ones who get killed.

45
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:44,600
Or those who want
to leave the system.

46
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:46,267
What are you saying, Bok?

47
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,733
I discovered...

48
00:01:48,867 --> 00:01:50,167
that Donabel...

49
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:53,633
also worked as an escort.

50
00:01:53,767 --> 00:01:56,200
Maybe she doesn't like
that job anymore.

51
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:57,367
She wants to leave.

52
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:59,833
That's why she was killed,
right?

53
00:01:59,967 --> 00:02:02,367
Sir, we need to stop this.

54
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,467
The other contestants
might get involved too.

55
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:07,333
That's why it's good that you're
joining the contest, Bobby.

56
00:02:07,467 --> 00:02:10,167
You'll be our key
to solving this case.

57
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:12,467
And once we solve this,

58
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,767
there's a good chance
that it'll point us...

59
00:02:14,933 --> 00:02:17,267
who the real head
of the syndicate is.

60
00:02:54,067 --> 00:02:55,700
- What's taking so long?
- Still thinking.

61
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:56,867
- Oh, come on.
- Checkmate!

62
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,767
Three.

63
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,100
Was that a checkmate?

64
00:03:00,233 --> 00:03:02,000
Ever tried eating a fist, Bro?

65
00:03:02,133 --> 00:03:03,567
What's your problem?

66
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:04,900
You're not from here.

67
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:06,433
Are you lost?

68
00:03:06,567 --> 00:03:08,667
So what if we're lost?

69
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,167
Wherever we end up,

70
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:11,233
that's our territory.

71
00:03:11,367 --> 00:03:13,800
These guys are cocky!

72
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:15,533
Maybe they find you small,
Betong.

73
00:03:15,667 --> 00:03:16,467
Are you Betong?

74
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,333
Even if you the three
of you gang up,

75
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:20,433
we'll still beat you down!

76
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,400
Is that so?

77
00:03:21,533 --> 00:03:22,633
Oh, he wants to fight back...

78
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:23,800
Oh, what?

79
00:03:23,933 --> 00:03:25,333
- Come on! What?
- Don't interfere.

80
00:03:25,467 --> 00:03:26,533
These two are mine!

81
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:27,567
- Try us, Betong!
- Oh, come on! Let's go!

82
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:29,033
Come on, let's go here, come on!

83
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,367
Here, come closer!

84
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,033
- What? Come here!
- Come on!

85
00:03:32,167 --> 00:03:34,600
- Hey! Let's go!
- Betong, come on!

86
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:40,367
Come on!

87
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,533
Let's go!

88
00:03:42,667 --> 00:03:45,233
Come on! Let's go!

89
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:46,700
Let's go!

90
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,700
- What?
- Go ahead!

91
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,400
You think I'm scared
of what you're holding?

92
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:53,600
Oh, really?

93
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,067
Are you ready for me
to smash your faces!

94
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:56,367
What? Try it!

95
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,133
Just make sure we don't look
like you, okay?

96
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,433
That's enough.

97
00:04:02,567 --> 00:04:03,967
What? Are you going to join?

98
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:05,467
Go ahead.

99
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,200
- Beat him!
- Beat him up!

100
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:12,133
Go ahead!

101
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:15,367
So, Bobby, later,

102
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,200
head straight to the pageant.

103
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:20,400
No one should suspect
we know anything.

104
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,167
Noted, Sir.

105
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:24,733
Garcia and I are going back
to the Station.

106
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:27,267
Chief and I will plan
our next move.

107
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:30,700
Tell Samson to just observe.

108
00:04:30,867 --> 00:04:33,900
Let us know if you notice
anything unusual.

109
00:04:34,033 --> 00:04:35,100
Yes, Sir.

110
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:38,733
Don't make a move
until we're there.

111
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,233
Understood, Sir.

112
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:42,167
Wait a minute, Tonyo.

113
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:44,733
Why did you suspect
I was the one?

114
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:47,800
A witness came to
the station earlier.

115
00:04:47,933 --> 00:04:50,067
He said he was a regular
customer of Donabel.

116
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,467
He claimed that the last time
they were together,

117
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,533
she was dropped off
at your condo.

118
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:59,933
I don't even know why
we believed that guy.

119
00:05:00,067 --> 00:05:01,167
Just by looking at him,

120
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:05,333
he doesn't seem like he could
afford escort services.

121
00:05:05,467 --> 00:05:07,633
They pointed it to me.

122
00:05:07,767 --> 00:05:09,600
They want to frame me up here.

123
00:05:09,733 --> 00:05:12,033
They already know we're
investigating this.

124
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:15,600
That means they're watching us.

125
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:17,267
What's your plan, Sir?

126
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:21,800
We need to make them believe
that their plan is working.

127
00:05:21,933 --> 00:05:23,500
I have an idea.

128
00:05:23,633 --> 00:05:26,400
The question is, Jared...

129
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:29,333
are you good at acting?

130
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:39,100
Wait a minute!

131
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:41,367
Hey, where are you taking me?

132
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:42,900
You have no evidence!

133
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:44,900
I'm innocent!

134
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:46,600
Let me go!

135
00:05:48,467 --> 00:05:50,167
- This is wrong!
- Here!

136
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:51,367
What is it?

137
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,767
Stop struggling! Go inside!

138
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,367
Mayor...

139
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,800
we can move freely now.

140
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:10,000
They bought
what we were selling.

141
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:11,767
It worked.

142
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:15,100
<i>I understand you're worried
because he's your sister.</i>

143
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:17,100
<i> But you also know our clients.</i>

144
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:18,533
<i> That's my problem now.</i>

145
00:06:18,667 --> 00:06:20,367
<i> I'll take care of them.</i>

146
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:22,367
<i> The important thing is,</i>

147
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,800
<i>no one finds out
about our operation.</i>

148
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:29,433
<i>Now, the police are here
because of Donabel's case.</i>

149
00:06:29,567 --> 00:06:31,267
<i> Let's keep it that way.</i>

150
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,933
<i> Mayor, I have a plan.</i>

151
00:06:37,067 --> 00:06:39,267
<i> Let's keep those two busy.</i>

152
00:06:41,133 --> 00:06:42,833
<i> They want a suspect?</i>

153
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:47,633
<i>I'll plant one
for them to follow.</i>

154
00:06:51,633 --> 00:06:52,933
Okay, Mayor.

155
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:54,767
I'll keep you posted.

156
00:06:57,567 --> 00:07:00,533
Boy, you impressed me
with your acting.

157
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:02,100
Thanks, Boss.

158
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:05,133
Next time, call me again if you
need someone for a job, okay?

159
00:07:05,267 --> 00:07:08,533
What I need now
is for you to hide.

160
00:07:08,667 --> 00:07:10,100
Okay?

161
00:07:10,233 --> 00:07:13,067
If I see you here again,

162
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,267
I'll finish you myself.

163
00:07:15,433 --> 00:07:18,167
- Is that clear?
- Yes.

164
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:19,833
All right.

165
00:07:33,033 --> 00:07:33,667
All right!

166
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,367
- No!
- What?

167
00:07:37,567 --> 00:07:40,300
We didn't come here
to cause trouble.

168
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:43,633
We just want to know
who ordered you to beat me up.

169
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:44,667
That's it?

170
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,300
That's all you want from me?

171
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:47,833
You made me tired for that.

172
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,167
We just didn't want to confront
you in your own turf.

173
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:51,567
We were being careful.

174
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,867
You know Vince, right?

175
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,533
You beat him up.

176
00:07:56,667 --> 00:07:59,100
You want to know who ordered
us to beat you?

177
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:03,667
What's funny?

178
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,700
Well, we're the same.

179
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:07,833
I don't know who gave
the order either.

180
00:08:08,767 --> 00:08:13,033
Hey, don't cover for them or
we'll take you to the precinct!

181
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:17,067
Do you know Telegram,
the chat app?

182
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,867
Yes, why?

183
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,533
That's where I got the job
from an unknown number.

184
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:26,133
Here's my phone.

185
00:08:28,733 --> 00:08:30,600
Search for it.

186
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:38,867
They sent you my picture
to beat me up?

187
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,467
I didn't have a problem with it.

188
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,600
It was a good gig,

189
00:08:41,733 --> 00:08:43,200
but I'm not stupid.

190
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:44,633
That's why you asked
for show money?

191
00:08:44,767 --> 00:08:45,767
Of course.

192
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,200
We needed to confirm
that it was legit.

193
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:50,033
So when we got the ten thousand,

194
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:51,267
I called the guys.

195
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,833
It's ten thousand pesos,
that's already enough for us.

196
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,433
Sorry, Bro.

197
00:08:55,567 --> 00:08:57,500
Just a gig. You know how it is.

198
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:04,500
<i>The subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

199
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:05,767
<i> - Please try again later.
-</i> What?

200
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:07,500
You can't reach them either,
right?

201
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:09,300
You know, for what
we did to you,

202
00:09:09,433 --> 00:09:11,533
even for five hundred pesos,
we'd do it.

203
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:12,900
What do you mean?

204
00:09:13,033 --> 00:09:14,500
You were paid a lot to do this?

205
00:09:14,633 --> 00:09:15,467
Yes!

206
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,067
That's ten thousand too.

207
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:20,067
And whoever ordered
to beat you up,

208
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,800
for sure, he's a big shot!

209
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:26,067
Give me my cellphone!

210
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:33,767
With the help of Bautista,
Torres, and De Jesus,

211
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:37,433
We were able to confirm
the one who killed Robles.

212
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:40,033
It's none other than Roman.

213
00:09:51,533 --> 00:09:53,333
Bautista...

214
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,700
I am so proud of you.

215
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:57,600
Do you know
how I feel right now?

216
00:09:57,733 --> 00:10:02,333
Like I just saw my eldest
graduate college.

217
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,300
- Thank you, thank you.
- Thank you, Sir.

218
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:08,033
Garcia, sit down.

219
00:10:10,867 --> 00:10:13,933
We all know we are hunting...

220
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:17,067
the mastermind of the syndicate
here in Calabari.

221
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,633
But the closer we get to him,

222
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:21,067
the more he slips away.

223
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:24,033
So, Bautista, De Jesus, Torres,

224
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:26,633
continue the search for Roman.

225
00:10:26,767 --> 00:10:28,767
- Copy, Chief.
- Copy, Chief.

226
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,100
Like what Chief said,

227
00:10:31,233 --> 00:10:33,800
this criminal is slippery.

228
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:36,000
And we discovered...

229
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:39,700
while investigating
Donabel Custodio's case...

230
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:42,267
that this is not just a simple
murder case.

231
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,633
With the help of Private
Investigator Jared,

232
00:10:44,767 --> 00:10:47,733
we found out
there's a high chance...

233
00:10:47,867 --> 00:10:51,700
this pageant is being used
for prostitution,

234
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:57,100
and the one running it is the
mastermind we've been chasing.

235
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,600
So we will carry out
an operation

236
00:11:02,733 --> 00:11:05,533
with the help of
Enriquez and Samson...

237
00:11:05,667 --> 00:11:08,167
who are part of the pageant.

238
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:10,067
This is it, guys.

239
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,200
Let's do our best for tonight.

240
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:17,100
Let's end the reign of crime
here in Calabari.

241
00:11:17,233 --> 00:11:18,600
Sir, yes, Sir!

242
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,600
Hey, Dude, wait.

243
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:32,133
So what now?

244
00:11:32,267 --> 00:11:34,367
Your opponent seems
to work professionally.

245
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,800
That's the thing, Dude.

246
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:37,867
I'm more worried about Faye.

247
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,167
Worry about yourself too.

248
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:43,033
You know, Bro, this is just
my advice to you.

249
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,500
You know, I love you very much.

250
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:47,567
If you're going to talk
to Miss Faye,

251
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:50,300
make sure it's just between
the two of you, text or call.

252
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:51,433
No one else.

253
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:55,567
Dude, just remember,
we're here for you.

254
00:12:07,067 --> 00:12:09,900
<i> How are you?</i>

255
00:12:10,033 --> 00:12:12,933
<i>I still have something to do,
Faye,</i>

256
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:16,600
<i>but I'm glad that
we were able to talk.</i>

257
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:20,633
<i> Can we meet?</i>

258
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:31,867
- Add2Cart.
- Any update, Roman?

259
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,200
Hey, Boss.

260
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:35,567
All good.
I already talked to Okoy.

261
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:38,533
Well, he really likes
your sister.

262
00:12:38,667 --> 00:12:40,233
There's nothing
we can do about it.

263
00:12:40,367 --> 00:12:43,133
If he really want her, let him
do it outside the event.

264
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:45,133
They'll implicate me.

265
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:46,533
Listen, Roman.

266
00:12:46,667 --> 00:12:49,633
No one makes decisions
without my go signal.

267
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:52,167
There are a lot
of big investors coming.

268
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:55,567
I want things to run
as smooth as possible.

269
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:59,300
Here's what you tell Okoy,

270
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:02,000
don't talk to me
during the pageant.

271
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:04,467
All communication
goes through you.

272
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,600
Yes, Mayor.

273
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:08,100
But just a little warning.

274
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:11,433
Okoy can be crazy sometimes.

275
00:13:11,567 --> 00:13:13,000
Be careful.

276
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,200
How are you doing here, Jared?

277
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:27,933
Are you okay?

278
00:13:28,067 --> 00:13:32,000
I'm sorry, but we can't take you
on the operation anymore.

279
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:35,100
I understand that.

280
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:40,033
By the way, Lieutenant Conde...

281
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:46,233
I know that the two of us
didn't get off to a good start.

282
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:51,233
But whatever you and Bobby have,
I hope you can fix it.

283
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:53,067
She's quite a catch.

284
00:13:56,233 --> 00:13:57,567
Thanks.

285
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:01,000
Tonyo...

286
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:03,733
keep Bobby safe.

287
00:14:08,067 --> 00:14:09,533
Of course.

288
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:13,467
Come on.

289
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,167
Lieutenant Garcia...

290
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:19,000
How was my acting?

291
00:14:19,133 --> 00:14:21,700
It's okay, you're good.

292
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:25,200
But between you and Tonyo,

293
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:26,467
I'd go with Tonyo.

294
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,733
He's best actor material.

295
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,967
Bok, that's enough. Let's go.

296
00:14:43,967 --> 00:14:46,800
You know, thank you, Selena.

297
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:49,133
I don't know...

298
00:14:49,267 --> 00:14:50,600
I look so pretty tonight,

299
00:14:50,733 --> 00:14:53,100
but I'm still nervous.

300
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:57,033
What are you saying?
That's normal for first-timers.

301
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:58,600
So what do we do?

302
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:00,367
I'm nervous too.

303
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,533
Why?

304
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:03,400
I don't want to mess up
during the Q&amp;A.

305
00:15:03,533 --> 00:15:04,800
I don't want to go viral.

306
00:15:04,933 --> 00:15:06,167
I don't want to go viral either.

307
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:07,867
I don't want to be embarrassed.

308
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,367
Stop thinking like that.

309
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,433
Let's just enjoy tonight.

310
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:13,900
- Yes.
- Just relax, okay?

311
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:16,733
That's right. You got this.

312
00:15:16,867 --> 00:15:19,700
How about you, Bobby,
aren't you nervous?

313
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:23,000
A little.

314
00:15:23,133 --> 00:15:25,000
How about you?

315
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:27,433
A little.

316
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:29,733
But I hope I win.

317
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:31,933
Because I'm the black sheep
of the family.

318
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:33,800
When my mother scolds me,

319
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,100
she always tells me...

320
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:38,433
that I haven't done
anything right.

321
00:15:38,567 --> 00:15:40,033
So,

322
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:42,667
if I win tonight,

323
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:46,367
I hope she thinks that
I've done something right.

324
00:15:48,167 --> 00:15:49,767
Wow, so dramatic!

325
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:51,467
Oh, my. I'm sorry, Bobby.

326
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,767
- That's okay.
- I'm so dramatic.

327
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:58,033
Teresa, Peach, Apple,

328
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,733
I have a feeling

329
00:15:59,867 --> 00:16:03,667
that tonight will be a good
night for all of us.

330
00:16:09,967 --> 00:16:11,567
- Hello?
- Bobby!

331
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:12,767
<i>What's up?
What's taking so long?</i>

332
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:14,300
<i> No news yet?</i>

333
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:16,667
<i> Yes! We can't wait anymore!</i>

334
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,367
It's going to start soon.

335
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,833
I'm about to get dressed.

336
00:16:20,967 --> 00:16:22,600
Where's grandmother?
Let me talk to her.

337
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:24,433
<i>- Call her, call her.
- Hey, Captain!</i>

338
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:26,100
<i> Captain, it's Bobby!</i>

339
00:16:26,233 --> 00:16:27,600
<i> Come on! It's Bobby!</i>

340
00:16:27,733 --> 00:16:29,467
<i>Hurry up! Here!
There she is!</i>

341
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,167
<i> Bobby?</i>

342
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:33,500
<i> Bobby, my grandchild, Bobby!</i>

343
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:34,867
<i> Bobby!</i>

344
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,900
<i> I hope you win!</i>

345
00:16:37,033 --> 00:16:38,433
<i> If only I had money,</i>

346
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,733
<i> I'd bet everything on you!</i>

347
00:16:40,867 --> 00:16:42,200
<i>- Oh!
- Yes!</i>

348
00:16:42,367 --> 00:16:45,600
Oh my, good thing you don't
have any, Grandmother.

349
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:49,233
Because we all know
I won't win here.

350
00:16:49,367 --> 00:16:52,133
But even if I don't win,

351
00:16:52,267 --> 00:16:54,667
I'm still the prettiest.

352
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:58,067
Because the grandchild
who is beautiful...

353
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:01,633
<i>Because the grandchild
who is beautiful...</i>

354
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:03,667
<i> What?</i>

355
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:05,267
<i> What?</i>

356
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,367
<i> Oh...</i>

357
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:09,367
<i>Got her looks
from her grandmother!</i>

358
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,500
<i>- Bobby, focus on that!
- Okay, Bobby.</i>

359
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:12,300
<i>-We'll take care of grandmother.
-Yes!</i>

360
00:17:12,433 --> 00:17:13,500
<i>- Break a leg!
- Good luck!</i>

361
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:15,533
<i> Beat them all!</i>

362
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,800
<i>- They're nothing!
- Yes!</i>

363
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:17,833
<i>- Okay!
- I'll smack them!</i>

364
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:19,600
<i> Good luck, my grandchild!</i>

365
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:20,800
<i> Good luck, my grandchild!</i>

366
00:17:20,933 --> 00:17:22,100
Go ahead, Bobby.

367
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:23,767
Do your best!

368
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:33,133
Because the grandchild
who is beautiful...

369
00:17:33,267 --> 00:17:36,833
got her looks from grandmother.

370
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:38,900
So, girls, are you ready?

371
00:17:39,033 --> 00:17:40,967
Because we're about to start
in one hour.

372
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,900
So be ready, and good luck
to all of you.

373
00:17:44,033 --> 00:17:45,767
See you later on stage.

374
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:51,767
This is for you, Grandmother.

375
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:09,600
Listen up, men!

376
00:18:09,733 --> 00:18:13,833
Let's cover the perimeter
because we don't know...

377
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:16,067
what's going to happen tonight.

378
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:19,833
So stand down
until further instructions.

379
00:18:19,967 --> 00:18:20,967
Is that clear?

380
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:23,200
Sir, yes, Sir!

381
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:26,333
Sir, I've spoken
to the hotel security.

382
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:31,233
Once we identify the suspect,
they'll help us.

383
00:18:31,367 --> 00:18:32,533
Good job, Conde.

384
00:18:38,667 --> 00:18:39,600
It's better if we split
into two groups.

385
00:18:45,933 --> 00:18:48,233
Conde, what's the update?

386
00:18:48,367 --> 00:18:50,800
Sir, as of now, there's still no
update from Enriquez, Sir.

387
00:18:50,933 --> 00:18:53,567
Let's secure all exits.

388
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:55,667
You take the lead, Conde.

389
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:58,600
Yes, Sir!

390
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,333
Men, listen up!

391
00:19:02,567 --> 00:19:05,000
There are two major exits
in the hotel.

392
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:07,967
Garcia's team and mine will
handle the South exit.

393
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:10,233
Dizon and Noble's team...

394
00:19:10,367 --> 00:19:12,133
will secure the North exit.

395
00:19:12,267 --> 00:19:13,300
Copy, Bok.

396
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:15,133
As per Chief, no one moves...

397
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:17,300
until Enriquez gives an update.

398
00:19:17,433 --> 00:19:18,800
Enriquez will report directly
to me.

399
00:19:18,933 --> 00:19:20,200
That means...

400
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:22,767
all commands will come from me.

401
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,733
Remember...

402
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:27,367
we lie low here.

403
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,733
Don't make yourself
visible inside.

404
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:32,500
They might escape again.

405
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:37,433
Once Samson and Enriquez
identify their suspect inside,

406
00:19:37,567 --> 00:19:40,800
remember our primary
objective...

407
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:42,467
capture them alive.

408
00:19:43,167 --> 00:19:45,633
Because our real mission here...

409
00:19:45,767 --> 00:19:50,033
is to identify the real leader
of this syndicate.

410
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:51,100
Is that clear?

411
00:19:51,233 --> 00:19:52,233
Sir, yes, Sir!

412
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:54,000
Men, let's go!

413
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:56,167
- Sir.
- Be careful.

414
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:06,933
So, Ladies,
before the pageant begins,

415
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:09,867
I want to introduce you
to our sponsors.

416
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:14,267
Please be nice to them
because without them,

417
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,700
there wouldn't be
a Miss Calabari.

418
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:21,600
And who knows, they might open
new opportunities for you.

419
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:23,767
So, Ladies, let's go.

420
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:24,833
Let's go.

421
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:28,900
Charlie, Bobby,
stay here for now.

422
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:30,667
Ladies, follow me.

423
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,000
Follow me.

424
00:20:41,033 --> 00:20:42,600
Thank you.

425
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:46,233
Gentlemen, our beloved sponsors,

426
00:20:46,367 --> 00:20:51,467
please welcome our candidates
of Miss Calabari 2025.

427
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:23,133
- Francis, congratulations.
- Mr. Eliseo.

428
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:27,167
Teresa?

429
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:30,300
Mr. Randy Eliseo.

430
00:21:30,433 --> 00:21:33,233
Pleasure to meet you,
Mr. Eliseo.

431
00:21:33,367 --> 00:21:34,867
Nice to meet you too.

432
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,600
May I lead you to my table?

433
00:21:36,733 --> 00:21:38,333
Sure.

434
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,333
Is there anything I can get you?

435
00:21:46,467 --> 00:21:48,300
- I'm good, Sir.
- Okay.

436
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:50,433
So you guys live together
in the apartment?

437
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:51,800
Yes.

438
00:21:51,933 --> 00:21:53,833
How nice of you, girls.

439
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:59,100
Well, me and my partner here,
we're from CTV.

440
00:21:59,233 --> 00:22:01,233
We are talent scouts.

441
00:22:01,367 --> 00:22:04,200
- CTV? As in Calabari TV?
- Yes!

442
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:05,433
- Yes!
- Yes.

443
00:22:05,567 --> 00:22:07,067
Do you watch our show?

444
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,500
Oh yes, I do watch it.

445
00:22:09,633 --> 00:22:13,167
There are so many handsome
and beautiful actors.

446
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:14,900
I know, right?

447
00:22:15,067 --> 00:22:17,900
Which brings me to my question.

448
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:24,367
What would you guys feel
if we hire you as talents?

449
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:26,500
Oh, as in we'd become actors?

450
00:22:26,633 --> 00:22:27,867
Yes.

451
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,400
Yes. If your performance
is good, why not?

452
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:34,333
And of course,
we're having this go-see...

453
00:22:34,467 --> 00:22:36,767
- at Richie's house.
- Yes.

454
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:39,433
Next Saturday,
if you guys could come,

455
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:41,000
- this might be the move
- Yes!

456
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:43,767
that will change your lives!

457
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:45,800
Oh, my God! Yes, yes, we'll go.

458
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:47,267
- We can go, right?
- Yes.

459
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:48,633
Just tell us the address.

460
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:50,000
- We'll be right there.
- Of course, of course.

461
00:22:50,133 --> 00:22:51,567
We'll be expecting you.

462
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:52,233
Yes.

463
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:53,433
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

464
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:06,667
Why didn't they
take us with them?

465
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:08,400
Bobby...

466
00:23:08,533 --> 00:23:10,633
open your eyes.

467
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:13,533
Something strange
is going on here.

468
00:23:13,667 --> 00:23:17,233
We need to gather information
about those sponsors.

469
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:26,500
You know, the reason why
I'm actually here

470
00:23:26,633 --> 00:23:30,900
is to find the next brand
ambassador for my company...

471
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:33,033
and I spotted you,

472
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:35,300
and I know you'd fit the role.

473
00:23:35,433 --> 00:23:36,633
Really?

474
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:38,000
Yes.

475
00:23:38,133 --> 00:23:39,233
Thank you.

476
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:41,867
Actually, whether you win
or lose,

477
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:44,633
you don't have to worry
about anything.

478
00:23:46,267 --> 00:23:49,300
Because I will take care of you.

479
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,467
I'm sorry.

480
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:58,167
Waiter!

481
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:01,167
Wine?

482
00:24:02,567 --> 00:24:03,933
Just water.

483
00:24:08,867 --> 00:24:10,467
Sir Francis!

484
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:11,467
Charlie.

485
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:13,600
Who are those other contestants
talking to?

486
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:16,467
And why aren't we included?

487
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:20,733
Those are our various sponsors
and businessmen.

488
00:24:20,867 --> 00:24:23,800
Well, most of them are here to
look for someone to represent

489
00:24:23,933 --> 00:24:25,500
their brands.

490
00:24:25,633 --> 00:24:27,300
And actually, they've already
pre-selected

491
00:24:27,433 --> 00:24:30,267
the ladies they want to meet.

492
00:24:30,433 --> 00:24:34,200
And I'm sorry to say, girls,
you weren't chosen.

493
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:36,600
Will you excuse me?

494
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:10,100
- Bobby!
- That's my grandchild!

495
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:11,733
That's my grandchild!

496
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:13,833
Tonyo, I'm just really
nervous right now.

497
00:25:13,967 --> 00:25:15,367
Do you really think this is it?

498
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:17,033
If we move correctly,

499
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:20,233
there's a big chance we'll catch
whoever's behind all of this.

500
00:25:20,367 --> 00:25:21,967
I've already talked to Teresa.

501
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:23,067
She seems stubborn.

502
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,600
What do you want us to do?

503
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:27,067
Then let's go with the fast
and forceful approach, right?

504
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,300
One of our clients

505
00:25:28,433 --> 00:25:30,967
is planning to kidnap
the girl he bought.

506
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:33,267
<i>There are cops
inside your pageant.</i>

507
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,933
<i> We'll get caught.</i>

508
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:37,500
I have a bad feeling
about this pageant.

509
00:25:37,633 --> 00:25:40,133
I don't know what it is yet,
but something bad might happen.

510
00:25:40,267 --> 00:25:41,000
Find me.

511
00:25:41,133 --> 00:25:42,567
This medallion is mine.

512
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:44,000
No police, no plaque.

513
00:25:44,133 --> 00:25:45,167
Stop!

514
00:25:49,633 --> 00:25:51,000
You're under arrest!

515
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:52,133
For real?
